In a large bowl, combine the milk powder, sugar, flour and cocoa. Cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Freeze in an airtight container for up to 6 months or refrigerate for up to 3 months. To prepare fudge pops: In a saucepan, whisk 2 cups mix and water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 1-2 minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently. Remove from the heat; stir in vanilla. Cool slightly. Fill 3-oz. molds or cups three-fourths full; top with holders or insert Popsicle sticks. Freeze for up to 3 months. Yield: 10 fudge pops.